      <hedline>
        <hl1>Jerseyan Gored in Bull Run</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By DAVID W. CHEN</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Chen, David W</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John Convoy, New Jersey man, is in serious condition after being gored by bull during bull run in San Sebastian de Los Reyes, Spain (New Jersey Daily Briefing) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A New Jersey man was gored by a bull on Saturday during the final day of a bull run in San Sebastian de Los Reyes, a small town six miles north of Madrid, The Associated Press reported.</p>
        <p>The man, John Convoy, was in serious condition after a bull hooked him in the leg and groin. The Spanish news agency EFE identified Mr. Convoy as a former United States Marine from New Jersey, but no further information was available.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A New Jersey man was gored by a bull on Saturday during the final day of a bull run in San Sebastian de Los Reyes, a small town six miles north of Madrid, The Associated Press reported.</p>
        <p>The man, John Convoy, was in serious condition after a bull hooked him in the leg and groin. The Spanish news agency EFE identified Mr. Convoy as a former United States Marine from New Jersey, but no further information was available.</p>
        <p>In 1995, a 22-year-old man from a Chicago suburb was the killed during a bull run in Pamplona, Spain, the first such fatality in 15 years.</p>
        <p>NEW JERSEY DAILY BRIEFING</p>
